OL,7,FAn estimated #3 billion "and counting"
OL,8,Fof capital investments in gas
OL,9,Fpipelines is scheduled to be recovered
OL,10,Ffrom bill payers after 2050 ` when
OL,11,Fthere will be no customers left on the
OL,12,Fnetwork, the report warns.
OL,14,FIn the coming years, network costs
OL,15,Fwill be split between a dwindling
OL,16,Fnumber of customers, pushing up prices
OL,17,F` with vulnerable people such as
OL,18,Frenters and low-income households
OL,19,Fleast able to make the shift away from
OL,20,Fgas.
